parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic overdrive switch can cause the transmission to jerk and struggle to operate properly, leading to a loss of control of the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The "HOLD" light on the dashboard flashes constantly
the transmission jerks and struggles to operate properly
the vehicle feels unstable and difficult to control
especially when taking small turns or maintaining high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission shifts into another gear unexpectedly
the vehicle makes a loud noise while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle makes a knocking noise when making sharp or slow turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coolant Reservoir Crack and Head Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the coolant reservoir can cause coolant to leak, leading to engine overheating, which can result in a blown head gasket, engine damage, and potentially a car fire.
Engine stalling can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System and Engine Valve Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty electrical systems and engine valves can cause a range of problems, including engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
Worn or faulty belts can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power.
Oil pump failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power.
Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Radiator Malfunction and Multiple Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator malfunction can cause engine overheating, and multiple component failure can increase the risk of accidents.
The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause inadequate braking, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage. It can also result in premature wear of brake pads and rotors.
symptoms: The rear brake caliper locks up

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Braking and Airbag Deployment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate braking and airbag deployment issues can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The failure of the braking system can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, and the failure of airbags to deploy can exacerbate the severity of injuries.
